<blockquote>
<p><strong>Standardization becomes critical in a connected world.</strong> If you never come into contact with your faraway neighbors, it doesn‚Äôt especially matter whether you use the same measurements, operate by the same clock, or have the same size windows in your workplace. The Industrial Revolution, however, had the effect of shrinking the world‚Äîjourneys which would once have been unthinkably long could now take place in the space of weeks, or even days. And for that, there needed to be cooperation along the line.</p>
